tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketonuria, glucosuria), suggesting possible renal dysfunction or acute kidney injury. Elevated chloride and low COâ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Hemoglobin A1c is low, ruling out chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible acute or chronic kidney disease and metabolic derangements.
